BRIEFING:
RATHER BENIGN CONDITIONS EXPECTED THROUGH THIS AFTERNOON, WITH SOUTHEASTERLY WINDS DEVELOPING ACROSS THE STATE. ASIDE FROM A FEW SHOWERS OVER MAUI COUNTY RESULTING IN SOME LOCAL MVFR, EXPECT MAINLY VFR CONDITIONS THROUGH THIS AFTERNOON.
A STRONG LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM WILL APPROACH FROM THE NORTHWEST LATER TODAY, THEN PASS NORTH OF THE ISLANDS TONIGHT INTO FRIDAY. A STRONG COLD FRONT WILL PUSH DOWN THE ISLAND CHAIN LATE TONIGHT THROUGH FRIDAY. EXPECT CONDITIONS TO DETERIORATE TOWARDS MVFR OR LOWER OVER THE WESTERN HALF OF THE STATE THIS EVENING AND SPREAD INTO THE EASTERN HALF OVERNIGHT AND INTO FRIDAY. STRONG SOUTHERLY WINDS, HEAVY RAIN, AND A FEW THUNDERSTORMS ARE POSSIBLE TONIGHT AND FRIDAY.
THREAT: NO SIGMETS IN AREA OF OPERATION.
